'''Henry Township''' is one of thirteen [[Civil township|townships]] in [[Henry County, Indiana|Henry County]], [[Indiana]], [[United States|USA]].  As of the [[United States Census, 2000|2000 census]], its population was 23,859.<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/DTTable?_bm=y&-context=dt&-ds_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_P001&-CONTEXT=dt&-tree_id=4001&-all_geo_types=N&-geo_id=06000US1806533124&-search_results=01000US&-format=&-_lang=en United States Census Bureau American FactFinder]</ref>

==Geography==
Henry Township covers an area of {{convert|36.87|sqmi}}; of this, {{convert|0.26|sqmi}} or 0.7 percent is water. The streams of Baker Branch, Boulder Run, Castle Run, Dark Run, Elliott Cemetery Run, Elliott Run, Grove Run, Hillcrest Brook, Little Blue River, Memorial Creek, Mound Run, Penns Run, Pink Creek, Saint Creek, Saint Johns Drain, Sky Run, Sugar Drain, Suncrest Brook, West Leg Westwood Run, Westwood Run and Wood Brook run through this township.

===Cities and towns===
* [[New Castle, Indiana|New Castle]] (the county seat)

===Unincorporated towns===
* [[Belmont, Henry County, Indiana|Belmont]]
* [[Van Nuys, Indiana|Van Nuys]]
* [[Westwood, Henry County, Indiana|Westwood]]
(This list is based on USGS data and may include former settlements.)

===Adjacent townships===
* [[Prairie Township, Henry County, Indiana|Prairie Township]] (north)
* [[Liberty Township, Henry County, Indiana|Liberty Township]] (east)
* [[Franklin Township, Henry County, Indiana|Franklin Township]] (south)
* [[Spiceland Township, Henry County, Indiana|Spiceland Township]] (southwest)
* [[Greensboro Township, Henry County, Indiana|Greensboro Township]] (west)
* [[Harrison Township, Henry County, Indiana|Harrison Township]] (west)
* [[Jefferson Township, Henry County, Indiana|Jefferson Township]] (northwest)

===Cemeteries===
The township contains three cemeteries: Elliott, Saint Johns and South Mound.

